President Trump held a Cabinet Room meeting to discuss immigration and funding for the border wall. He hailed the recent Supreme Court ruling on immigration as a victory for the American people and the Constitution. He emphasized the need for strong borders and vetting of people coming into the country. The President also expressed his desire to increase funding for the border wall in order to stop drugs and unwanted individuals from entering the country. Various Senators and Representatives in attendance spoke about the progress being made on appropriations bills and the importance of border security. The President also addressed concerns about his trade policies, stating that tariffs can be a positive measure and that negotiations with other countries are ongoing. He reaffirmed his commitment to protecting American industries and technologies from unfair practices by other countries.